David Keatts commented on [low] have punctuation be optional in auto complete so that Rakdos Lord of Riots would autocomplete to Rakdos, Lord of Riots, etc.: "getting the react site to do this was relatively easy, and it now ignores commas dashes and single quotes.

getting the python/js site to do this was quite difficult. I did ultimately end up switching from bootstrap3-typeahead to corejs-typeahead.  it took much trial and error but it works great now.  all search terms are tokenized, similar to how elasticsearch tokenizes text (e.g. Abzan Kin-Guard becomes `{value: "Abzan Kin-Guard", tokens: ["abzan", "kin", "guard"]}`.

from the UI side, everything is the same.  most users won't notice anything changed."
